cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span class="ͼg">&lt;img</span><span> </span><span class="ͼf">src</span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span class="ͼc">"images/cleaning.jpg"</span><span> </span><span class="ͼf">alt</span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span class="ͼc">"Teeth Cleaning"</span><span class="ͼg">&gt;</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div><div class="flex w-full justify-end px-3 mt-1" data-code-block-feedback-row="true"></div></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="795" data-end="852">If the name is different, the image <strong data-start="831" data-end="851">will not display</strong>.</p>
<h3 data-section-id="1dt5td0" data-start="854" data-end="882">If you don't want images</h3>
<p data-start="883" data-end="956">You can also <strong data-start="896" data-end="923">remove the <code data-start="909" data-end="916">&lt;img&gt;</code> tags</strong> and the website will still work.</p>
<hr data-start="958" data-end="961">
<p data-start="963" data-end="1060">✅ For <strong data-start="969" data-end="992">internship projects</strong>, I recommend adding <strong data-start="1013" data-end="1036">3–5 relevant images</strong> so the UI looks better.</p>
